\mu = np = 0.27\cdot 2000 = 540
\sigma = \sqrt{npq} = \sqrt{2000\cdot 0.27\cdot 0.73} \approx 19.85
P\left(500 < x < 600\right) = P\left(\dfrac{500-540}{19.85} < z < \dfrac{600 - 540}{19.85}\right) = P\left(-2.01 < z < 3.02\right) = P(-2.01 < z < 0) + P(0 < z < 3.02) \approx (0.5 - 0.0222) + (0.9987 - 0.5) = 0.9765
97.65\text{%}
